r chain guard.","Fixings","Lower chain guard","Remove the axle shaft and the final drive unit (see ","Final Drive/Rear Hub and Bearings - Removal",").","Place the axle shaft/brake disc assembly to one side.","Release the fixings and remove the hugger.","Fixings","Hugger","Remove the rear suspension unit (see ","Rear Suspension Unit - Removal",") and support the swinging arm.","Detach the chain from the output sprocket.","Release the fir tree and remove the covers for the swinging arm spindle.","Fir tree","Cover, left hand side shown","Remove the swinging arm spindle nut and washer from the right hand side. Discard the nut.","Partially withdraw the swinging arm spindle from the left hand side, to allow access to the frame adjuster on the right hand side of the frame.","Spindle","Using ","service tool T3880104",", loosen the frame adjuster.","T3880104 - Swinging Arm Adjuster Wrench","Frame adjuster","Withdraw the swinging arm spindle from the left hand side and remove the swinging arm, together with the drive chain.","Support the drive chain while the swinging arm is being removed to protect it from contamination.","If the swinging arm is to be replaced, remove the drive chain (see ","Drive Chain Replacement",").","Swinging arm spindle","Remove the large circlip securing the caliper carrier to the hub and remove the carrier.","Remove the wheel bearing/hub from the left hand side of the swinging arm.","Circlip","Caliper carrier","Hub","Swinging arm","Carrier fixing","Remove the outer seal and bearing sleeve from the left hand side.","Remove the seal and spacer from the right hand side.","Release the circlip and remove the two ball bearings by drifting through from the left.","Remove the spacer tube.","The needle roller bearing and inner seal in the right hand side of the arm cannot be removed undamaged.","Remove the right hand bearing and inner seal by drifting through from the left.","Seal","Spacer","Circlip","Ball bearings","Spacer tube","Inner seal","Bearing sleeve"